
A JOIN clause is used to combine rows from two or more tables, based on a related column between them.
It is used to join the 2,3,4 table (used for retrive the data from multiple tables).
 
 Condition Check :- if you join the two table make sure that both table any one column is same name.

 Types of Join:-

 1) Inner Join
 2) Outer Join (Left outer join,Right outer join,Full Outer Join)
 3) Cross Join
